==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abalone
<hw>Ab`a*lo"ne</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧b`⟦adot⟧*l⟦omac⟧"n⟦esl⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A univalve mollusk of the genus
<gen>Haliotis</gen>. The shell is lined with mother-of-pearl, and used
for ornamental purposes; the sea-ear. Several large species are found on
the coast of California, clinging closely to the rocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

